                  CONNECTING INSTRUMENTS TO THE VAX                   _________________________________ 







1. SUMMARY OF KNOWN SPEED CONSIDERATIONS WHEN INTERFACING TO VAX 




1.1 CAMAC - VAX     ___________ 

At AAO, Helen Davies has received successfully 1 KHz interrupts.  The
recommended UNIBUS limit is 100 Hz. 


1.2 IEEE-488 - VAX     ______________ 

IEEE-488 interfaces from both DEC and NATIONAL claim DMA rates of 200
Kbytes/sec. 

IEEE-488 bus extenders - NATIONAL claim 200 Kbytes/sec, H-P claim  50
Kbytes/sec. 



2. EXISTING UKIRT INSTRUMENTS WITH KNOWN SPEED PROBLEMS 




2.1 UKIRT CGSII and 8-banger     ________________________ 

The computer generates the chopper control signal and  inputs  the  8
channels  of  data  every  chopper  half-cycle,  which  means  20 Hz.
Interrupts have to be serviced within about 5 msecs. 





                                                                 ADN/3.1                           2                           ADN/3.1



2.2 UKIRT Speckle interferometry     ____________________________ 

The computer is used to generate a ramp to  drive  the  chopper,  and
samples  the signal at each point of the ramp. The timing is achieved
by interrupting the computer at about 200  Hz  using  a  programmable
clock. 


2.3 UKIRT High-speed photometry     ___________________________ 

This requires measurements without  beamswitching  at  up  to  a  few
hundred Hz. 



